</taxonomicName>
, some marpissines). The thoracic window is also different from the pale area on the top of the thorax seen in other baviines (e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="9FEC2584AB5107D0D3BF30840D82AF77" class="Arachnida" family="Pittosporaceae" genus="Bavia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bavia nessagyna" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nessagyna">
<emphasis id="76118FB572257C17C608A5FA1F02F548" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Bavia nessagyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in alcohol), where it is neither as pale nor does it extend so far posteriorly as in 
<taxonomicName id="30FEF2FE13B0C5DDB9DD4372973F3D55" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Padillothorax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Padillothorax" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="21AD12442DB3EA631F75AB6A061D8051" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Padillothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="23919F72E9DE31BAE1652D2D7FF2BA82" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1885" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stagetillus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stagetillus" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F9498A684F680D337ACEE940F5EA0B40" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Stagetillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., and 
<taxonomicName id="5D7415D8C1D129AFD21E0402D1E3987F" authority="Maddison, 2020" authorityName="Maddison" authorityYear="2020" class="Arachnida" family="Pittosporaceae" genus="Maripanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maripanthus draconis" order="Apiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draconis">
<emphasis id="8B3DC65D3FAFBB15F57F477D52AFAEAB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Maripanthus draconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a pale thorax, but it is not framed by dark, as most of the thorax is pale. Palp is also distinctively simple: embolus narrow, pointing distally (i.e., appears erect in standard ventral view), fused to the tegulum, with no tegular fold covering its base as in 
<taxonomicName id="473B2C6928A2C446897C6251D2AC71D8" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1877" class="Arachnida" family="Pittosporaceae" genus="Bavia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bavia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1C6E42E950F0F88A0516FC04643C2754" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Bavia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and many 
<taxonomicName id="DE76F913194459CB74A3930C6F9AA385" authority="Caleb &amp; Sankaran, 2019" authorityName="Caleb &amp; Sankaran" authorityYear="2019" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Indopadilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Indopadilla" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E17D04E26F1178955F4D8E2DF5E36147" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Indopadilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Epigynal openings anterior with simple copulatory ducts proceeding posteriorly. Abdomen with distinct transverse bands. First legs distinctly the longest. Male endite with lobe or sharp corner, unlike 
<taxonomicName id="4451CF5B6AF46C79DE73DF2F00B75BE3" authority="Caleb &amp; Sankaran, 2019" authorityName="Caleb &amp; Sankaran" authorityYear="2019" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Indopadilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Indopadilla" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="45B4A607636FD69FA19474765751A840" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Indopadilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(whose endite is rounded, without lobes or corners).
</paragraph>
